QUESTION 14 OF 16
CORRECT
What is the difference between Date.now and Date.now() when adding a "createdAt" to a model
Date.now() executes the function immediately, Date.now waits for the function to be called.
QUESTION 15 OF 16
CORRECT
What does "mongoose.model("Movie", MovieSchema)" do
It tells Mongoose that the "Movie" model will have the shape of the MovieSchema
QUESTION 16 OF 16
CORRECT
On the video #3 .4 why did we import the models in the init.js file
Because we need to make the mongoose connection 'aware' of the Models that we will save in the future.